[2] Washington State (Walla Walla County)
Date: Tue 6 Jan 2015
Source: Walla Walla Union-Bulletin [edited]
http://t.union-bulletin.com/news/2015/jan/06/flu-pertussis-cases-climb-walla-walla-valley


Health officials today [6 Jan 2015] said Walla Walla County is experiencing a greatly increased number of cases of pertussis, best known as whooping cough. "We're seeing pertussis in high school students. We've had a 5-month-old infant diagnosed, but we're now receiving a number of reports in adolescents," he said. "And that's particularly worrisome."

Today's pertussis immunization was developed to be safe for infants "but the immunity is not particularly long-lived," Crowder said. "We're trying to find a better vaccine for adolescents and adults."

[Byline: Sheila Hagar]

