*****
[3] Alaska
Date: Sun 4 Jan 2015
Source: News Miner [edited]
http://www.newsminer.com/features/health/more-than-cases-of-whooping-cough-reported-in-in-alaska/article_55b07906-94b4-11e4-bab0-2f9260573e86.html


Between January and November 2014, Alaska had 130 reported cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, according to the Alaska Department of Health and Social Services. September 2014 had the highest number of incidences, 38, followed by October 2014, with 22.

While a significant drop from the 356 cases reported in 2012, it was still significantly more than the 26 reported in 2011. Epidemiologist Louisa Castrodale said the large number of reported cases is likely a reflection of a growing baseline and increased screening.

Of the 130 cases reported, 92 were from Interior Alaska. Castrodale said the large percentage of pertussis from the Interior is likely due to increased screening after a confirmed case.

