[5] California (Santa Barbara County) infant fatality
Date: Wed 14 Jan 2015
Source: Fox News, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.foxnews.com/health/2015/01/14/santa-barbara-county-infant-dies-from-whooping-cough/


A newborn baby has died from whooping cough in Southern California, the 4th death since the beginning of 2014 as the state deals with an epidemic. The Santa Barbara County Public Health Department announced the death Tue 13 Jan 2015. It says the baby was 25 days old, caught the bacterial infection last year [2014] and died this month [January 2015].

The state Department of Public Health says 3 other infants died in 2014, including 2 who caught the illness in 2013. State health officials have recorded 10 831 cases that were contracted in 2014. It's the worst epidemic to hit the state in 7 decades. Authorities attribute the increase to better detection and to the use of new vaccines that have fewer side effects but also don't protect as long.

--
